{
  "stem": "13874.3",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 88,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But quite a few others, they were interred in the Isle of Man and stayed there for two years, and so on.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 88,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "In that-- in the internment camp in that Isle of Man was not only people from the camp, but refugees, domestics mostly, who worked as domestics in England.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 88,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "That was the only type of job which was permitted.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 89,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Between England and Ireland.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 90,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I had very little contact, so I cannot complain much.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 91,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Half a year.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 92,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 92,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We were-- it was a holding camp, waiting to get to [INAUDIBLE] to get out of it one way or another.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 92,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was just a temporary holding to get out of Germany until we were able to get someplace else.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 93,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It happened [INAUDIBLE] and [?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 93,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Steve ?] [INAUDIBLE] a friend of mine was also there.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 93,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And he also came to the United States, and we've still stayed friends.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 93,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I knew a few local people.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 93,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But otherwise they were just shadows.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 94,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Not at all.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 95,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I got my permit to enter the United States.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 95,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My quota number came up, and I went to-- had to go to the consulate in London.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 95,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I got my passport and visa, and I came to the United States.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 96,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That was-- I left England on the 30th of January, 1939, and I arrived on the 12th of February.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 97,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "On a British ship.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 98,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, it was the Georgic.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 99,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Georgic-- G-E-O-R-G-I-G-- C.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 99,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "G-I-G.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 99,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was a Cunard liner.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 100,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "One of the reasons I couldn't get there after I got out of Dachau, and I had enough money on me directly, from cash.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 100,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So I could walk into a Cunard line office and building and bought a first class ticket on the Queen Mary to the United States, open-- an open ticket.",
      "word_count": 29
    }
  ],
